HEADWORD: Prototype
<hw>Pro"to*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from L.
<ets>prototypus</ets> original, primitive, Gr. <?/, <?/; <?/ first + <?/
type, model. See <er>Proto-</er>, and <er>Type</er>]</ety> <def>An
